<DocsLayout
  title="Installation"
  description="Build Alterm from source with Cargo, or package a release for Linux, macOS, or Windows."
>
  <p>
    Alterm is currently distributed as source. Building it takes one Cargo command. Packaged
    installers (<code>.deb</code>, <code>.rpm</code>, Homebrew, Winget) are on the roadmap.
  </p>

  <h2>Build from source</h2>
  <p>Requires <strong>Rust 1.80+</strong>. Clone the repository and install the binary:</p>
  <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/rhask87062/alterm.git
cd alterm
cargo build --release
cargo install --path alterm</code></pre>
  <p>
    The <code>alterm</code> binary is then available on your <code>PATH</code> (under
    <code>~/.cargo/bin</code>).
  </p>

  <div class="note">
    <p>
      First launch creates <code>~/.config/alterm/config.toml</code> from the defaults. See
      <a href="../configuration">Configuration</a> for what you can change.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2>Packaging a release</h2>
  <p>The <code>packaging/</code> scripts produce native bundles per platform.</p>

  <h3>Linux</h3>
  <pre><code>./packaging/build-release.sh linux</code></pre>
  <p>Produces:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><code>dist/alterm_&lt;version&gt;_&lt;arch&gt;.deb</code></li>
    <li><code>dist/alterm-&lt;version&gt;-linux-&lt;arch&gt;.tar.gz</code></li>
  </ul>

  <h3>macOS</h3>
  <pre><code>./packaging/build-release.sh macos</code></pre>
  <p>Produces <code>dist/Alterm.app</code> and <code>dist/alterm-&lt;version&gt;-macos-&lt;arch&gt;.pkg</code>.
    Requires Apple <code>pkgbuild</code>.</p>

  <h3>Windows</h3>
  <pre><code>pwsh -File .\packaging\windows\build-installer.ps1</code></pre>
  <p>
    Produces <code>dist\alterm-&lt;version&gt;-windows-x64-setup.exe</code>. Requires Inno Setup
    (<code>ISCC.exe</code>) on your <code>PATH</code>.
  </p>

  <h2>Planned distribution</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><code>.deb</code> (Debian / Ubuntu) and <code>.rpm</code> (Fedora / RHEL)</li>
    <li>Homebrew formula (macOS)</li>
    <li>Winget / MSIX (Windows)</li>
    <li>Flatpak (cross-distro Linux)</li>
  </ul>
</DocsLayout>
